A series of plans will probably best explain to the reader the astronomieal terms used by Lucretius in this and other passages. The explanations of the plans are largely drawn and condensed from Mr. Duff's account of the Celestial Sphere.

The axis is the direction of the earth’s rotation. As we do not notice this rotation the heavenly bodies seem to revolve round us. The sun therefore seems to rise and set every day. It also seems to travel round the sky once a year owing to the fact that the earth revolves on its orbit round the sun. The ancients believed that the earth was at rest in the centre of the universe.
